\f0\fs32 \cf2 Where the two texts run parallel in the trailer, however, is the action. The clip of the audience, for instance, shows people with immediate and terrified responses. The shots from the primary text, on the other hand, show restrained occurrences such as a sheet moving or door closing by itself. Benson-Allot notes that the audience\'92s horrifying reaction and the primary text\'92s minimalist action are at \'93odds\'94 with each other (2013, p. 188). The mixture fuels the mystery of the item the audience is watching. Viewers observing the trailer will likely want to know why the audience is responding with such urgency to clips where, on the face of it, nothing that scary is happening. 
